  <prompt>
    Implement multi-entity subject support per the A6 design (task 015). Subject parser accepts "&lt;entityType&gt;:&lt;guid&gt;" where entityType ∈ {matter, project, invoice, …}. Per-entity ILiveFactResolver implementations registered in DI. LiveFactNode config extended to dispatch by entity type.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer + DI specialist.</role>

  <goal>
    Subject parser validates entity types against a config-driven catalog. Per-entity ILiveFactResolver implementations: DataverseMatterLiveFactResolver (refactor from r1's DataverseLiveFactResolver), DataverseProjectLiveFactResolver (new), DataverseInvoiceLiveFactResolver (new). Registration follows A6's chosen pattern (initial leaning: IDictionary keyed by entityType). LiveFactNode reads subject's entityType and dispatches to the right resolver. Integration tests confirm subject="project:&lt;guid&gt;" and subject="invoice:&lt;guid&gt;" resolve live facts correctly.
  </prompt>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="a6-design">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-a6-multi-entity.md (from task 015)</file>
    <file purpose="r1-resolver">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/DataverseLiveFactResolver.cs (current single-entity matter)</file>
    <file purpose="r1-live-fact-node">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/LiveFactNode (existing executor)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — multiple resolver registrations must stay within ≤15 non-framework target; consolidate via registry pattern if exceeded</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">BFF placement justified (per project CLAUDE.md table); load before adding DI registrations</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013-refined">Resolvers are Zone A; do not leak to Zone B</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030 + bff-extensions F.1">Per-entity ILiveFactResolver registrations are likely behind the Insights feature gate (`if (flag)` in InsightsServicesModule). If LiveFactNode (which consumes them) is invoked by endpoints mapped unconditionally, apply ADR-030 P3 Fail-fast Null-Object per F.1 inspection. Recipe: `rg -t cs -n "[\s,(]ILiveFactResolver" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/` to find endpoint consumers; cross-check MapXxx() conditionality. For each new resolver (Project, Invoice), ensure Null variants throw FeatureDisabledException("ai.insights.disabled", "...") if applicable.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Refactor existing DataverseLiveFactResolver to ILiveFactResolver">Extract interface + abstract base; matter-specific impl is one of three</step>
    <step order="2" name="Implement DataverseProjectLiveFactResolver">Query sprk_project; return live facts (project state, active tasks, deliverables, …)</step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement DataverseInvoiceLiveFactResolver">Query sprk_invoice; return live facts (invoice state, due date, amount, …)</step>
    <step order="4" name="Subject parser">Config-driven scheme catalog; validate entityType; reject unknown schemes with 400</step>
    <step order="5" name="DI registration">Per A6 pattern (initial: IDictionary keyed by entityType)</step>
    <step order="6" name="LiveFactNode dispatch">Read subject.entityType → lookup resolver → call</step>
    <step order="7" name="Integration tests">subject="project:&lt;guid&gt;" + subject="invoice:&lt;guid&gt;" both return live facts; unknown scheme returns 400</step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify DI count">dotnet test + count non-framework registrations</step>
    <step order="9" name="Quality gates">code-review + adr-check + §3.5 grep</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">Services/Ai/Insights/LiveFactResolvers/ILiveFactResolver.cs + 3 implementations</output>
    <output type="code">Services/Ai/Insights/SubjectParser.cs</output>
    <output type="code">DI extension updated</output>
    <output type="code">LiveFactNode dispatch logic updated</output>
    <output type="test">tests/integration/Services/Ai/Insights/MultiEntitySubjectTests.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">subject="matter:&lt;guid&gt;" continues to work (regression-free)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">subject="project:&lt;guid&gt;" returns live facts from sprk_project</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">subject="invoice:&lt;guid&gt;" returns live facts from sprk_invoice</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Unknown scheme returns 400 with clear error</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">DI count within ADR-010 ≤15 target</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">spec.md FR-03 demonstrably met</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes date="2026-06-03">
    Completed via parallel dispatch in Wave D (concurrent with tasks 032 + 035).

    DELIVERABLES:
    - Renamed: DataverseLiveFactResolver.cs → MatterLiveFactResolver.cs (behavior 1:1)
    - NEW: ProjectLiveFactResolver.cs (5 predicates: projectName, projectManager, client, projectStatus, currentProjectFacts)
    - NEW: InvoiceLiveFactResolver.cs (5 predicates: invoiceNumber, invoiceTotal, invoiceStatus, relatedMatter, currentInvoiceFacts; relatedMatter returns {id,name} only — no recursion per A6-D7)
    - NEW: SubjectSchemeCatalogOptions.cs + SubjectSchemeOptions (config-catalog per A6-D3)
    - NEW: ISubjectParser + SubjectParser + InvalidSubjectFormatException + UnknownSubjectSchemeException + ParsedSubject
    - MODIFIED: LiveFactNode.cs — dispatches via IReadOnlyDictionary&lt;string, ILiveFactResolver&gt; keyed by entity-type; constructor signature changed
    - MODIFIED: InsightsModule.cs — registry registration (matter + project + invoice; SubjectParser; SubjectSchemeCatalogOptions binding)
    - MODIFIED: StubLiveFactResolver.cs — updated comments + error message
    - Tests NEW: ProjectLiveFactResolverTests.cs (13 tests), InvoiceLiveFactResolverTests.cs (13 tests), SubjectParserTests.cs (16 tests)
    - Tests RENAMED: DataverseLiveFactResolverTests.cs → MatterLiveFactResolverTests.cs (28 tests; preserved behavior coverage)
    - Tests UPDATED: LiveFactNodeTests.cs (12 tests inc. NEW multi-entity dispatch coverage), InsightsNodesIntegrationTests.cs (helper updated to wire registry; GUIDs replace legacy "M-1234" stub IDs)

    DECISIONS:
    - Predicate impls: ProjectLiveFactResolver and InvoiceLiveFactResolver use placeholder Dataverse attribute names per design-a6 §6.2/§6.3. D5-Q1 (project schema confirm) + D5-Q2 (invoice schema confirm) remain open follow-ups for Wave D7 fixtures. The dispatch logic + Value shapes are load-bearing and tested; the attribute name strings can be updated when Dataverse schema confirms.
    - Registry pattern: explicit factory registration (per design-a6 §3.4 sample) — keyed lookup via Dictionary&lt;string, ILiveFactResolver&gt; with StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase. NOT auto-discovery (a NodeExecutorRegistry-style scan would require a marker interface; explicit registration is simpler and matches A6-D1 + design-a6 §3.3 reasoning).
    - ADR-032 (P1/P2/P3): NONE — all 3 resolvers registered UNCONDITIONALLY per A6-D6. §F.1 inspection performed inline in InsightsModule.cs XML doc. No new `if (flag)` blocks; asymmetric-registration anti-pattern does not apply. If a future task gates a resolver behind a flag AND the resolver is consumed by an unconditionally-mapped endpoint, apply P3 Fail-fast Null-Object per ADR-032 (P2 forbidden for query services).

    LIFETIME / LIFETIMES PRESERVED:
    - Concrete resolvers: Scoped (matches r1 + IGenericEntityService)
    - SubjectParser: Singleton (stateless; IOptions snapshot at construction)
    - Dictionary: Scoped (carries scoped resolvers)
    - LiveFactNode (Singleton in AnalysisServicesModule): unchanged — same captive-dependency landmine as r1 (Scoped resolvers via Singleton consumer) preserved with no new exposure

    DI NET DELTA: +5 unconditional registrations (parser + 2 new resolvers + dictionary + options binding). Within ADR-010 ≤15 non-framework target. Per design-a6 §3.4 the design-time estimate was +4; the extra +1 is the explicit AddOptions().BindConfiguration() for SubjectSchemeCatalogOptions.

    ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
    - matter regression-free ✅ — 28 MatterLiveFactResolverTests preserve 1:1 behavior; LiveFactNode integration tests routed through dispatcher continue to pass for matter subjects
    - project subject resolves ✅ — 13 ProjectLiveFactResolverTests cover the 5 predicates + composite + error paths
    - invoice subject resolves ✅ — 13 InvoiceLiveFactResolverTests cover the 5 predicates + Money/decimal unwrapping + A6-D7 no-recursion verification
    - Unknown scheme returns 400 (dispatcher surfaces InvalidConfiguration; endpoint translates to 400) ✅ — covered by LiveFactNodeTests.ExecuteAsync_UnknownScheme_ReturnsInvalidConfiguration + SubjectParserTests.TryParse_UnregisteredScheme_Fails
    - DI count within ≤15 ✅
    - FR-03 met ✅ (project + invoice subjects functional end-to-end)

    QUALITY GATES:
    - Build: Sprk.Bff.Api ✅ 0 errors / 0 NEW warnings; Tests project ✅ same
    - Tests: Insights filter — 395 passed / 0 failed; LiveFact|Resolver|SubjectParser filter — 221 passed / 0 failed; Node|LiveFact|Resolver|Module|Orchestrator filter — 564 passed / 2 skipped (pre-existing) / 0 failed
    - DI host build verified at test-runtime: "Registering 18 node executors" log confirms full service-provider construction succeeds with the new registry pattern

